    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nNot sure what exactly is causing the problem, but I can reproduce it reliably using the steps below:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/4657140/4bbd040c-b565-48f2-be61-adc43b201d19\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim --clean\r\n:e file.txt\r\n<C-f><C-f>\r\n:vnew\r\n:tabnew\r\n:tabclose\r\n:set number\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNo window should scroll when I execute `:set number`\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.9.4\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno, 9.0.1544\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 13.5.1\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.29.0\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nhomebrew",
